# Legal accuracy (required)

When creating or editing public legal content:

## Case law

- Never invent case citations or holdings.
- Every `R v …`, `[YYYY] EWCA`, or `(YYYY) … Cr App R` reference must link to BAILII or appear in `data/legal-case-registry.json`.
- Summarise holdings accurately; link to primary source.

## PACE and Code C

- Verify section/paragraph numbers against GOV.UK Code C 2023 or legislation.gov.uk before publishing.
- Do not attribute rights to wrong sections (e.g. s.58 = right to legal advice, not evidence-weight rules).
- Distinguish: fitness to interview ≠ fitness to plead; Code breach ≠ automatic exclusion.

## Sources

- Public blog posts and substantive guides must end with `<h2>Sources</h2>` and official links.
- Minimum two official domains in Sources for substantive legal posts (`gov.uk`, `legislation.gov.uk`, `cps.gov.uk`, `bailii.org`).

## After editing

```bash
node scripts/sync-blog-index.mjs
npm run audit:legal
npm run test:legal
```
